				caption: '',
				content: "‘And made short work of it’; literally, ‘and he ran thence, and scattered it’. The Hebrew text is emended by some critics so as to mean ‘he carried it away’ instead of ‘he ran’."
			},
					552: {
				id_comment: 552,
				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
				content: "vv. 15-18: see III Kg. 13.2. ‘That was Israelite born’; literally, ‘that came from Samaria’. The old prophet lived in Bethel, and the reference to Samaria is probably meant to imply that he belonged to Israel, not to Juda."
			},
